<i>one of the ring of island
fortresses protecting Japan</i>

11:35.529 --> 11:38.280
<i>300 miles away.</i>

11:38.281 --> 11:41.699
<i>On April 1st, 1945,</i>

11:41.700 --> 11:45.204
<i>a U.S. invasion fleet of nearly 1,500 ships,</i>

11:45.205 --> 11:49.333
<i>a landing force of 182,000 people,</i>

11:49.334 --> 11:53.587
<i>that's 75,000 more than
Normandy, approached Okinawa.</i>

11:53.588 --> 11:57.466
<i>What came next was what Okinawans called</i>

11:57.467 --> 12:00.428
<i>a typhoon of steel.</i>

12:04.932 --> 12:07.226
<i>Having island hopped across the Pacific,</i>

12:07.227 --> 12:11.522
<i>Allied forces saw Okinawa as a
key base for fleet anchorage,</i>

12:11.523 --> 12:14.358
<i>troop staging and air operations for the final push</i>

12:14.359 --> 12:16.985
<i>into the Japanese mainland and victory.</i>

12:16.986 --> 12:20.030
<i>The fighting was brutal for both sides.</i>

12:20.031 --> 12:23.116
<i>The cost in lives and resources
