Thank you for going easy on me.

34:54.592 --> 34:58.220
Awesome.

34:58.221 --> 35:01.891
So I've given up many vices in my life.

35:01.892 --> 35:06.896
Many shameful, filthy, guilty pleasures

35:06.897 --> 35:10.399
that I used to like that I will...

35:10.400 --> 35:12.150
that I just don't do anymore.

35:12.151 --> 35:18.156
Uh, cocaine, heroin, prostitutes,

35:18.157 --> 35:21.744
the musical stylings of Steven Tyler.

35:21.745 --> 35:25.748
I put aside these childish things, as it were.

35:25.749 --> 35:29.668
In favor of a newer, more mature me.

35:29.669 --> 35:32.296
But there is one shameful secret.

35:32.297 --> 35:35.091
One thing I just can't give up.

35:35.092 --> 35:38.636
One thing I keep coming back to
every time I come back to Japan.

35:38.637 --> 35:43.891
One thing that still has an unholy grip on me.

35:43.892 --> 35:48.479
For no reason that I can gather.

35:48.480 --> 35:51.858
It's the convenience store
formerly of mere Akron, Ohio,

35:55.236 --> 35:59.573
that mutated into a massive Japanese chain.

35:59.574 --> 36:03.494
Behold the wonder that is Lawson.

36:03.495 --> 36:05.871
What is it exactly about this place?

36:05.872 --> 36:11.251
It's got its tentacles so deep
into my heart and my soul.

36:11.252 --> 36:14.339
♪

36:22.347 --> 36:26.351
Where are you? I know you're around here somewhere.

36:29.187 --> 36:31.772
Pillows of love.

36:31.773 --> 36:34.274
Egg salad from Lawson.

36:34.275 --> 36:36.318
Need a beverage.

36:36.319 --> 36:39.322
♪

36:55.213 --> 36:58.507
<i>In Naha, you would be advised to avoid</i>

36:58.508 --> 37:01.552
<i>International Avenue unless you're homesick</i>

37:01.553 --> 37:02.721
<i>for fellow Americans.</i>

37:04.222 --> 37:07.599
<i>Head down the side streets, shuttered storefronts</i>

37:07.600 --> 37:09.685
<i>give way to packed izakayas.</i>

37:09.686 --> 37:12.563
<i>A few beers, and somebody breaks out a shamisen,</i>

37:12.564 --> 37:15.274
<i>and the good times begin.</i>

37:18.195 --> 37:21.030
<i>People go out here. And after pounding your fists</i>

37:21.031 --> 37:22.907
<i>and feet into hardened meat hooks</i>

37:22.908 --> 37:26.577
<i>and shitting out bone chips,
you can drop by Dojo Bar,</i>

37:26.578 --> 37:30.789
<i>James' refuge where some of the
island's most esteemed masters</i>

37:30.790 --> 37:32.791
<i>and their students come for what's recognized</i>

37:32.792 --> 37:34.418
<i>internationally as a cure</i>

37:34.419 --> 37:39.339
<i>for all martial-arts related ailments: alcohol.</i>

37:39.340 --> 37:41.633
Would you like a drink? -I
think I would like a beer

37:41.634 --> 37:43.844
and maybe a shot of something.

37:43.845 --> 37:45.889
I do have a little shot of something.

37:49.642 --> 37:51.061
That's a big snake.

37:52.311 --> 37:55.272
The sake is like the spirit of Okinawa.

37:55.273 --> 37:58.609
Is this sake or whiskey? -This is sake.

37:58.610 --> 38:00.194
This is Okinawa sake,

38:00.195 --> 38:02.362
so like mainland Japanese sake

38:02.363 --> 38:03.781
but then they distill it like whiskey.

38:03.782 --> 38:06.909
So it becomes stronger and with a little age.

38:06.910 --> 38:10.287
It's been in here with the snake maybe three years.

38:10.288 --> 38:14.500
So all of the essence of the
snake has gone into the alcohol.

38:19.881 --> 38:23.384
♪

38:27.305 --> 38:30.224
There seems to be a conflict of interest here.

38:30.225 --> 38:32.684
You train karate very seriously.

38:32.685 --> 38:35.771
Yeah. -Um, I mean,

38:35.772 --> 38:39.150
should you people be drinking?
This is what I'm asking.

38:39.151 --> 38:43.195
Where is the point of diminishing returns?

38:43.196 --> 38:46.490
There are many teachers who don't drink,

38:46.491 --> 38:49.743
but Awamori is intrinsic to the Okinawan culture.

38:49.744 --> 38:52.496
Right. -Most enjoy Awamori

38:52.497 --> 38:55.291
as part of their lifestyle, in the same way karate

38:55.292 --> 38:56.751
is part of our lifestyle.

38:59.796 --> 39:02.924
They're saying, please eat.
Less talking, more eating.

39:05.302 --> 39:07.469
Sashimi of, well, let's just say

39:07.470 --> 39:09.721
it's an animal you like.

39:09.722 --> 39:13.350
This is horse meat. -Horse? All right.

39:13.351 --> 39:17.396
Thank you. Good.

39:19.774 --> 39:22.067
Good. And this? -Neigh.

39:22.068 --> 39:22.568
Goat.

39:29.159 --> 39:31.243
Oh, that's good.

39:31.244 --> 39:35.539
<i>Pure protein for people who need it and pork belly,</i>

39:35.540 --> 39:39.836
<i>some pickled pigs ears, and baked yam.</i>

39:41.379 --> 39:44.173
I watch a lot of mixed martial arts.

39:44.174 --> 39:48.593
I watch a lot of jujitsu. My daughter trains.

39:48.594 --> 39:50.804
Mostly jujitsu, but some standup.

39:50.805 --> 39:54.808
Some of the most exciting
fighters that I've seen lately

39:54.809 --> 39:58.896
who really show the most heart are women.

39:58.897 --> 40:05.028
Is there... is there a future for women in karate?

40:15.705 --> 40:18.874
Yeah, yeah.

40:18.875 --> 40:21.211
He has a female student here tonight.

40:25.131 --> 40:27.174
This is Yaya.

40:27.175 --> 40:32.096
Tony is asking what's the future
for women in traditional karate?

40:32.097 --> 40:36.725
When I first started karate,
I didn't know this world,

40:36.726 --> 40:40.187
and now I'm learning karate,

40:40.188 --> 40:44.442
as the performance and also life.

40:47.862 --> 40:51.531
Everything is all about love.

40:51.532 --> 40:57.246
And karate is showing you if
you have this kind of power

40:57.247 --> 41:01.083
and the ability to perfect yourself,

41:01.084 --> 41:06.672
your family, you can be really kind.

41:07.548 --> 41:09.883
That's about Okinawa.

41:09.884 --> 41:15.181
Okinawa people, I think, always
have this love to everybody.

